         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Supply by rental of Sterile Cleanroom Garments</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2017/S 246-514853</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="98311000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Supply by Rental, contract for Terminally Sterile Cleanroom Clothing for pharmaceutical sterile production units, x 8. Clothing and footwear, coveralls and accessories.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="98311000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKM82"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>NHS Greater Glasgow and Clyde Sites.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Supply by rental, contract for terminally sterile cleanroom clothing for pharmaceutical sterile production units, x 8. Clothing and footwear, coveralls and accessories. There are a number of aseptic facilities within NHSGG&amp;C (National Health Service Greater Glasgow and Clyde) that prepare sterile injectable medicines. Due to the nature of this provision the Board is required to meet specific ISO/EU GMP standards to minimise microbiological and particulate contamination. There is a requirement for pharmacy operators to be suitable attired in accordance with the above regulations. The Board therefore requires the provision of sterile and non-sterile cleanroom clothing complaint with, as a minimum, EU Grade B, C and D as appropriate. All garments and associated equipment must be sterile where required as well as individually packaged and traceable.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Technical</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>50</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_COST>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Commercial</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>50</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_COST>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">24</DURATION>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>Option for 2 year extension.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <LEFTI>
            <ECONOMIC_FINANCIAL_INFO>
               <P>With reference to ESPD question 4B.6 — NHSGG&amp;C will use its financial evaluation matrix to assess the financial stability of tenders. Tenderers should complete the evaluation matrix spread sheet included in the tender documents and confirm they meet the minimum requirement score. Tenderers with a Score of 50 and above will be deemed to have evidenced satisfactory financial stability. Tenderers should be able to provide financial accounts when requested by NHSGG&amp;C.</P>
